	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary82.jpg"/>
				<dateline>Saturday <date when="1862-06-28"/>28.</dateline>
				<p>A <name type="weather">cloudy day of rain</name> this afternoon. <persName
						cert="high" key="John Foster"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper055"
						type="real">Lt. Foster</persName>
					<orgName>Co. E</orgName> returned from home - brought me a <objectName
						type="readables">letter</objectName> from <persName key="John Blair Linn"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper051"
						>John</persName>. He came on the <objectName type="ship"
						>Cossack</objectName> which brought us a large <objectName>
						mail</objectName>. I had a letter from <persName>Em Hayes</persName> and one
					from [?] &amp; <persName key="John Hummel"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper177"
						>Hummel</persName> acknowledging his <objectName type="readables"
						>receipt</objectName> of the $60 we sent for the purpose of getting the
						<objectName>body</objectName> of <persName key="Lt. Lanig"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper151"
						>Lanig</persName> home. <persName>Old Christ</persName> the sutler was very
					particular in weighing some <objectName type="food">cheese</objectName> for
						<persName> John Miller</persName> this evening. <persName key="John Miller"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper176"
						>Miller</persName> told him he was as particular as old [Pehoch?]. How’s
					that. Why he would brush the flies’ feet when they came out the sugar box for
					fear they’d waste it. <persName key="Charley Shriner"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper178"
						>Charley Shriner</persName>, after whom the “Shriner guards” <orgName>Co.
						E</orgName> are called sent them a demi john of <objectName type="drink"
						>whisky</objectName>, &amp; this evening, <orgName>Co. E</orgName> feels
					good on this <objectName type="equipment">glass</objectName> of <objectName
						type="grog">grog</objectName>. There seems to be preparations for a march.
					We are ordered to report our effective men for a sharp march - the reliant ones
					number 578, though I could report bare 30 rank &amp; file. We were ordered to
					have 60 rounds of <objectName type="equipment">ammunition</objectName> each. I
					think it is merely precautionary. We have pap<objectName type="readables"/>ers
					to the 25th,but they are bare of the news we wait for though they tell us of
					victory at <placeName>White River</placeName> &amp; its sad accident on the
						<placeName> Mound City</placeName>. Did not we know that the rebels lie so,
					we would fear a repulse at <placeName> James Island</placeName>. No. 6. We have
					sent all our sick to the hos<objectName type="building"/>pital. </p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
